    <section>
        <title>Roles</title>
        <para>
            When a user needs to know what needs to be worked on, he/she needs a screen that quickly shows a 
            list of pending tasks.  This list will just contain a brief description (or an abstract) of the real task.  
            It's just the minimum information required by the user to understand the task that is pending, without interacting 
            or retrieving the full structure of the task.
        </para>
        <para>
            A task list that is only a summarized view of the pending tasks allows the user to choose which tasks in the list 
            to start working on first.  We can say that a task list is an entry point for the users to understand what they 
            need to do.
        </para>
        <para>
            This module is in charge of handling all the human interactions from the company and the external entities.  
            This module will only interact with Human Task Component started by the Core module. Version 3 implements this 
            module as a web application which all users can access in order to interact. Future versions will include different 
            clients to demonstrate that the task can be completed from mobile devices.
        </para>
